<body>
<table width="98%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" align="center">
  <tr> 
    <td><p class="text"><span class="pageHeader">Showing Custom Labels and tool 
        tips for entities</span></p></td>
  </tr>
  <tr> 
    <td><p class="text">You can show custom labels and tool tips for any entity 
        on the map. To do so, just add the following to <span class="codeInline">XML:</span></p></td>
  </tr>
  <tr> 
    <td> <p class="codeBlock"> &lt;map borderColor='005879' fillColor='D7F4FF' 
        numberSuffix=' Mill.' includeValueInLabels='1' labelSepChar=': ' baseFontSize='9'&gt;<br />
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;data&gt;<br />
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;entity id='NA' value='515' /&gt;<br />
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;entity id='SA' value='373' <strong>displayValue='C/S 
        America: 373 M' toolText='Central and South America: 373 Million (Including 
        External</strong> <strong>Islands)'</strong>/&gt;<br />
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;entity id='AS' value='3875' /&gt;<br />
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;entity id='EU' value='727' /&gt;<br />
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;entity id='AF' value='885' /&gt;<br />
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;entity id='AU' value='32' /&gt;<br />
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/data&gt; <br />
        &lt;/map&gt;</p></td>
  </tr>
  <tr> 
    <td><p class="text">Here, we've added out custom display value (label) and 
        tool text for South America Entity. When you view the chart, you'll get 
        the following output:</p></td>
  </tr>
  <tr> 
    <td><table width="95%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
        <tr> 
          <td><div align="center"><img src="Images/WorldMap6.gif" width="424" height="345" class="imageBorder" /></div></td>
        </tr>
      </table></td>
  </tr>
  <tr> 
    <td><p class="text">&nbsp;</p>    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr> 
    <td class="header">Hiding an entity's name </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="text">To hide an entity's name just set its displayValue as a blank space. Example: </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="codeBlock">&lt;map borderColor='005879' fillColor='D7F4FF' numberSuffix=' Mill.' includeValueInLabels='1' labelSepChar=': ' baseFontSize='9'&gt;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;data&gt;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;entity id='NA' value='515' <strong>displayValue=' '</strong>/&gt;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;entity id='SA' value='373' /&gt;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;entity id='AS' value='3875' /&gt;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;entity id='EU' value='727' /&gt;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;entity id='AF' value='885' /&gt;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;entity id='AU' value='32' /&gt;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/data&gt; <br>
&lt;/map&gt;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="text">In the above example, we've hidden the label of North America by setting its <span class="codeInline">displayValue</span> attrbute to a blank space. When you view this map, you'll get the following results: </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="text"><img src="Images/WorldMapNoLabel.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="313"></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="text">Note that North America is without any label now, though the tool tip will still function over it. </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="text">&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="header">Showing full labels and hiding the values</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><span class="text">To show full labels and hide the values on the map, use:<br />
        <br />
        <span class="codeInline">&lt;map &hellip; <strong>useSNameInLabels='0' 
    includeValueInLabels='0'</strong> &hellip; &gt;</span></span></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><img src="Images/WorldMap3.gif" width="400" height="230" class="imageBorder" /></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><p class="text">Now that we've played enough with the configuration options of the map, let's shift to the one of the most important aspects of FusionMaps - defining range based data and colors for better visual interpretation. </p>
        </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="text">&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
</table>
</body>
</html>
